summary: How would Harry react when his baby angel has to get her first shots ?
question: How would Harry react when his baby angel has to get her first shots ?
answer:
harry’s no stranger to needles and everyone knows that because of him being up to date with vaccines as his mum reminds, besides the fact that his extensive array of tattoos can tell that too.

but no, oh god no. when he sees baby angel getting a vaccine and she absolutely cries? think he couldn’t bear to look at another needle in his lifetime because he automatically thinks of his daughter’s face contorting in pain and crying hysterically.

after the shot, he couldn’t help but to grabe her right away and sway her in his arms, rubbing circles on her back as if it would relieve the mometary pain in her arm that was now lingering because it’s possible that she’s still a baby and they don’t exactly have a high pain tolerance because who would when a slight bump to the head can make them cry?

harry’s going nuts in his mind too, cradling her now close to his chest and he feels heartbroken at her physical pain.

“daddy would take your pain if he could, angel. we’re sorry. s’not gonna last forever. m’here. we’re here.”


bury me now will you

blog.name: wellthatwasaletdown
blog.title: Former Harrie Club
blog.description:
I created this as a place for former Harry fans who have recently been turned off by his promotion and solo rollout and are now just confused and want to have open discourse about it. I accept submitted posts and will post anything that is not derogatory or rude. Please keep it civil, we are here to talk not belittle each other. Attackers will be blocked.NEW: I will now be cutting off or removing submissions that are just repeating discussions that have already taken place. Please read back if you have a question, chances are it's been answered. As an added note, we are aware that not all Harries are angry people but we sometimes generalize due to character limits, apologies in advance but we know there are many lovely, kind, friendly Harries out there and we don't mean to offend you. <!-- Start of StatCounter Code for Tumblr -->

summary: The continued disconnect between the product Harry is trying to sell, himself, and his target market is concerning. The...
body: The continued disconnect between the product Harry is trying to sell, himself, and his target market is concerning. The disconnect between true Harry and his stage persona is also concerning. I think we’ve established that Jeff isn’t exactly the best at management but for the total input of Harry’s career, this output is mediocre and reveals their lack of understanding of their target audience. They probably haven’t defined a target audience in the first place. I guess the Gucci campaign was meant to appeal to the elite but if he wanted chart success and cultural significance, why appeal to one of the smallest demographics? They aren’t the people who will buy and stream his music, and more importantly they aren’t the people to listen to his music. On stage he’s made out to be a sjw but when presented with a social justice issue, he becomes a babbling fool. There’s so many plot holes in this narrative and hshq should be worried
